June 12 (Reuters) - The following corporate finance-related stories were reported by media:

* Imperial Tobacco Group Plc <IMT.L> is evaluating a deal for assets likely to be divested from Reynolds American Inc <RAI.N> and Lorillard Inc <LO.N> if the two U.S. tobacco companies proceed with a proposed combination, according to people familiar with the matter. [ID:nL2N0OS25C]  * Private equity-owned chemical distributor Univar Inc is poised to select Deutsche Bank Group AG <DBKGn.DE>, Goldman Sachs Group Inc <GS.N> and Bank of America Corp <BAC.N> to lead an initial public offering, according to people familiar with the matter. [ID:nL2N0OS27X]  * German conglomerate Siemens <SIEGn.DE> is in talks with Japan's Mitsubishi Heavy Industries <7011.T> on a possible joint bid for the energy assets of France's Alstom <ALSO.PA>, a source close to Siemens told Reuters on Wednesday. [ID:nB4N0NR00N]   For the deals of the day click on [DEALS/]